# 5 Day Sprint Framework - Cursor Rules
# Framework created by Omar Choudhry | 5daysprint.com

## Project: DesignFlow Pro
A comprehensive platform showcasing the Design4 framework - connecting strategy to execution for business leaders and strategists.

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 15 + TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
- Supabase (Database & Auth)
- Vercel (Deployment)

## Development Workflow
- MANDATORY: Use shadcn/ui components first before building custom
- Environment variables stored securely in .env.local (never commit)
- All API keys managed through environment variables
- Build locally before deployment: npm run build && npm run start

## Code Standards
- TypeScript strict mode enabled
- Use src/ directory structure  
- Import aliases: @/components, @/lib, @/app
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- ESLint for code quality

## Security Requirements
- Never store API keys in public files
- Use process.env.VARIABLE_NAME for all secrets
- Verify .env.local is in .gitignore
- All Supabase operations use client from @/lib/supabase

## File Structure
```
src/
├── app/           # Next.js app router
├── components/    # React components
│   └── ui/       # shadcn/ui components  
└── lib/          # Utilities & configs
```

## Environment Variables Available
- SUPABASE_URL, SUPABASE_ANON_KEY, SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
- USER_FIRST_NAME, PROJECT_NAME, PROJECT_OVERVIEW
- VERCEL_URL, GITHUB_REPO_URL, FIRECRAWL_API_KEY

